{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "23", "m": "03", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "14", "M": "47", "S": "24"}}, "news": [{"title": "India Accelerator to invest $5 million to double footprint in next 12-18 months", "para": "India Accelerator is set to invest $5 million to grow its coworking spaces across India. The company plans to double its presence in cities within the next 12 to 18 months. New centers are planned for Vadodara, Kolkata, Guwahati, and Bengaluru by the first half of 2026. This expansion aims to enhance community and coworking facilities nationwide.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/startups/india-accelerator-to-invest-5-million-to-double-footprint-in-next-12-18-months/129753353?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-144928/129753353.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "startups"}, {"title": "Lucknow civic body's budget 2026 okays no hike in property tax", "para": "Lucknow Municipal Corporation approved a Rs 1,253 crore budget for 2026-27, focusing on development without increasing property tax or parking charges. The civic body aims to boost revenue through better tax collection and expanding the tax base, with funds allocated for infrastructure improvements, sanitation, and beautification projects across all wards.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/lucknow-municipal-corporation-approves-2026-27-budget-with-no-property-tax-hike/129741802?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-84008/129741802.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Over 500 objects to proposed collector guideline rates for property in Indore", "para": "Nearly 500 objections were filed against proposed collector guideline rate hikes in Indore, with citizens and experts deeming increases unrealistic. Concerns include blanket hikes for bypass-adjacent land, outdated apartment valuations, and prohibitive costs for villages near new road projects. The District Evaluation Committee will review these complaints before forwarding the final proposal to Bhopal.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/controversial-100-hike-sparks-over-500-objections-to-indore-collector-guideline-rates/129741777?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-20288/129741777.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}]}